88 (e) The department of public health shall publish a guidance explaining the added sugars
89 warning icon requirement and how to comply, including specific directions for compliance at
90 chain restaurants’ physical locations and for menus on the internet.
91 (f) Reporting Requirement. Once every 90 days, the chain menu developer shall report to
92 the department the amount of added sugars in each menu item offered for sale in a covered
93 establishment, or that no changes to the menu information have been made since the last report.
